EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to education; requiring the Department of
Education to transfer certain data concerning pupils to an
archive maintained by the Department; requiring the
Department to destroy such data after a certain period of
time; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Department of Education to establish an automated
2 system of accountability information that records and tracks certain data relating to
3 the education system, including, without limitation, a system of unique
4 identification for each pupil and the results of the achievement of pupils. (NRS
5 385A.800) Existing law requires the board of trustees of each school district to
6 collect and provide certain data concerning pupils, as prescribed by the
7 Superintendent of Public Instruction, to the Department of Education. (NRS
8 385A.810, 385A.820)
9 This bill requires the Department to: (1) not later than 1 year after a pupil
10 graduates from a high school or otherwise ceases enrollment in a public school in
11 this State, transfer any data concerning the pupil to an archive of data concerning
12 pupils that is maintained by the Department; and (2) redact any personally
13 identifiable information, except for the birth date of the pupil, from the data before
14 making such a transfer.
15 Existing law: (1) creates the Committee to Approve Schedules for the Retention
16 and Disposition of Official State Records; (2) requires the Committee to review and
17 approve or disapprove the schedules for the retention and disposition of the official
18 state records of each agency, board and commission that is required to create such
19 schedules; and (3) prohibits an official state record from being disposed of in a
20 manner other than the schedule approved by the Committee. (NRS 239.073,
21 239.077, 239.080, 378.320) This bill: (1) provides that these provisions do not
22 apply to any data concerning pupils that is transferred to an archive maintained by
23 the Department pursuant to this bill; and (2) requires the Department to destroy
