THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 388 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The Department shall, not later than 1 year after a pupil
4 graduates from a high school or otherwise ceases enrollment in a
5 public school in this State, transfer any data concerning the pupil
6 to an archive of data concerning pupils that is maintained by the
7 Department. Any personally identifiable information, not
8 including the birth date of the pupil, must be redacted from any
9 data concerning the pupil before being transferred to the archive.
10 2. Notwithstanding the provisions of NRS 239.080 and
11 378.320, the Department shall, 10 years after a pupil whose data
12 was transferred pursuant to subsection 1 reaches 22 years of age,
13 destroy the data.
14 3. As used in this section:
15 (a) “Data” means any data concerning a pupil that is collected
16 by, or provided to, the Department pursuant to NRS 385A.800,
17 385A.810 or 385A.820, including, without limitation, a number
18 assigned to a pupil as part of a system of unique identification of
19 each pupil.
20 (b) “Personally identifiable information” has the meaning
21 ascribed to it in 34 C.F.R. § 99.3.
